# 🪐 NF-1 Language Specification & Technical Whitepaper
**Version:** 2.0.0-Stable | **Author:** Aditya Rai | **Org:** Aadi-Tech Enterprises
**Target:** Low-Resource 32-bit Stack Virtual Machines (x86 Optimized)

---

## 🛰️ 1. Abstract: The Zero-Footprint Protocol
NF-1 is a revolutionary, domain-specific programming language designed for **Extreme Resource Efficiency**. While modern languages consume gigabytes of RAM, NF-1 operates on a **Neural-Active Kernel** that maintains a persistent 0B memory leak state through the **Industrial Purge Protocol (IPP)**.

## 🏛️ 2. Architectural Layers

### 2.1 The Virtual Machine (NF-1 VM)
The VM utilizes a **Last-In, First-Out (LIFO) Stack Architecture**. 
- **Word Size:** 32-bit integers.
- **Memory Map:** 1024 addressable RAM cells with Global Persistence Heap.
- **Execution:** Bytecode-driven instruction set for deterministic performance.

### 2.2 The Aadi-Vector Graphics Engine
NF-1 integrates a hardware-accelerated vector drawing layer. Unlike standard libraries, NF-1’s `pen.down` and `move` protocols interface directly with the VM’s graphics buffer, enabling real-time rendering on legacy processors like the **Intel Core i3-3220**.

---

## 🛠️ 3. Semantic Instruction Set (SIS)

### ⚡ Power & Performance
| OpCode | Mnemonic | Cycle Cost | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `0x0D` | `@core.boost` | 1 | Shifts thread to high-priority hardware interrupts. |
| `0x14` | `eco.mode` | 0.5 | Throttles clock cycles to minimize CPU thermal load. |

### 🧠 Logic & Control Flow
| Mnemonic | Logic | Complexity |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `IF / ELSE` | Boolean Branching | O(1) |
| `LOOP.START` | Iterative Cycle | O(n) |
| `SET / GET` | Heap Persistence | O(log n) |

---

## 📊 4. Benchmarks & Stress Tests
Tested on **Aries 11 Systems** (Windows 10 Pro, 8GB RAM, 256GB SSD).

- **Boot Time:** < 50ms (from `brain.init` to active shell).
- **Memory Consumption:** Consistent 0B Leak (Validated via `mem.purge`).
- **Binary Size:** < 1MB (Full Compiler + VM).

---

## 🛡️ 5. Compliance & Safety Protocols
NF-1 incorporates the **Static Guard Protocol**. During development in Laksar, specific focus was placed on hardware safety, ensuring that low-level hardware interrupts do not conflict with power supply stability (Inverter/Earthing safety standards).

